cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on protecting connected vehicles against cyber-attacks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for detecting anomalies in vehicle behavior.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a generative model and a regression model for anomaly detection.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the need for adaptable data collection and the elimination of the need to retrain the model whenever a protocol changes.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the scalability of the approach from monitoring individual cars to serving large fleets.
